This privacy policy pertains to the JellyCast app.

JellyCast does not collect or access any personal information. No identifying information or user data of any kind is made available to third-parties.

JellyCast communicates only with:
- Your self-hosted Jellyfin server (configured by you)
- DLNA/UPnP devices on your local network (when DLNA is enabled)

No data is sent to external servers, analytics services, or third parties.

This Privacy Policy is effective as of October 17th, 2025 and will remain in effect except with respect to any changes in its provisions in the future, which will be in effect immediately after being posted on this page. We reserve the right to update or change our Privacy Policy at any time and you should check this Privacy Policy periodically. Your continued use of the Service after we post any modifications to the Privacy Policy on this page will constitute your acknowledgment of the modifications and your consent to abide and be bound by the modified Privacy Policy.

JellyCast is based on Findroid 0.15.3 by Jarne Demeulemeester.
JellyCast modifications by Jordi Guix (https://github.com/Jordigb44/JellyCast).
